@startuml urma_cw_lifecycle
title USE_URMA: C↔W build, retry, fallback, teardown (conceptual)

participant "ObjectClient\n(entry)" as OC
participant "ClientWorker\nRemoteApi" as CWA
participant "UrmaManager" as UM
participant "Worker" as W

== After RegisterClient and heartbeat ==
OC -> CWA: TryFastTransportAfterHeartbeat
CWA -> CWA: FastTransportHandshake
CWA -> CWA: InitializeFastTransportManager
CWA -> UM: init local if needed
UM --> CWA: OK
CWA -> CWA: AsyncFirstUrmaHandshake
CWA -> W: TryUrmaHandshake
W --> CWA: peer info / JFR path

== If first URMA is slow or fails ==
alt success
  CWA -> CWA: data path ready (UB/URMA)
else fail or timeout
  CWA -> CWA: set FLAGS_enable_urma false\nuse TCP
  opt retry scheduled
    loop while not stopUrmaHandshakeRetry_
      CWA -> CWA: ScheduleUrmaHandshakeRetry
      CWA -> W: retry handshake
    end
  end
end

== Teardown: normal exit or before switch Worker ==
CWA -> CWA: stopUrmaHandshakeRetry_ = true
CWA -> W: Disconnect when possible
W -> W: RemoveClient, symmetric URMA cleanup
CWA -> CWA: close socket, join recv thread\nreset urma_handshake pools
note right of CWA
  order matters on switch: finish Disconnect/dtor
  on old API before new RegisterClient + new URMA
  to avoid overlapping handshakes
end note

== Process shutdown (rare, separate from one CWA) ==
OC -> UM: app shutdown path
UM -> UM: Stop threads, clear maps
UM -> UM: UrmaUninit, munmap, dl cleanup

@enduml
